        How It Works
        The KOPLUS coding engine functions as a high throughput execution environment which aims to close the gap between creative music production and a technical architecture in script format.
        Firstly, The engine is operated through a 3-stage pipeline, starting with Lexical Analysis; the traffic controller that strip raw input into a string of 'tokens' that the system can understand as logic. 
        Such tokens are further divided based on syntactic and semantic rules into Abstract Syntax Tree (AST) creating a skeleton blueprint of what the intent of the code. That way the engine is able to boost functionality!
